24/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Meeting with a Bulgarian government delegation in the Vatican on Tuesday (23 May), Pope Benedict XVI voiced his support for the ruling coalition, describing it as a good example of co-operation among different political parties working towards strategic goals such as EU accession. 
The delegation, headed by Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev, is visiting Rome for celebrations of the Day of the Saint Brothers Cyril and Methodius. 
According to a press release from the Bulgarian cabinet, the pontiff praised Bulgaria as an example of tolerance and peaceful co-existence among different religions and ethnic groups. 
(BNR, Bulgarian Government Web site - 23/05/06)
